      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 126: bodyOverwrite from pluginData is trusted and rendered as the message body, but there is no validation of size or content before it enters the normal message rendering path. A plugin can replace a short message with arbitrarily large content, which may cause UI/memory issues, and may bypass assumptions made for original message bodies. Please apply the same constraints/sanitization used for normal message bodies before assigning it.\n```suggestion\nconst auto originalBody \u003d body;\nif (auto bodyOverwriteIt \u003d msg.pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n    bodyOverwriteIt !\u003d msg.pluginData.end() \u0026\u0026 !bodyOverwriteIt.value().isEmpty()) {\n    body \u003d sanitizeMessageBody(bodyOverwriteIt.value());\n}\n```",
